1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact R.S. 11:1903(B)(2) and to enact R.S. 11:1903(A)(5) and (H), relative
3 to the Parochial Employees' Retirement System of Louisiana; to provide for a district
4 court or parish court; to provide for membership; to provide for irrevocable
5 elections; to provide for transfer credits; and to provide for related matters.
6 Notice of intention to introduce this Act has been published.
7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
8 Section 1. R.S. 11:1903(B)(2) is hereby amended and reenacted and R.S.
9 11:1903(A)(5) and (H) are hereby enacted to read as follows:
10 §1903. Admission of certain entities as employers
11 A. The following entities may submit, for approval by the board of trustees,
12 a plan for extending the benefits of this Chapter to employees of the entity:
13 * * *
14 (5) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, any district
15 court or parish court in the state.
16 B. Each such plan or any amendment thereof shall be approved by the board
17 of trustees if it finds that such plan, or such plan as amended, is in conformity with
18 regulations of the board of trustees, except that no such plan shall be approved
19 unless:
20 * * *
21 (2)(a) It Except as provided for in Subparagraph (b) of this Paragraph,
22 it covers all services which are performed in the employ of the entity, by any
23 employees thereof, and it extends benefits to all employees of the entity.
24 (b) The board may approve the plan of an entity provided for in
25 Paragraph (A)(5) of this Section that does not cover all services performed in
26 the employ of the entity and does not extend benefits to all employees of the
27 entity.
