2 H.(1) Any employee of an entity provided for in Paragraph (A)(5) of this
3 Section hired before the employer extended the benefits of this Chapter to its
4 employees may make an irrevocable election to become a member of the system
5 if that employee is enrolled in another public retirement system covering the
6 same employment, has not participated in the deferred retirement option plan
7 of, or retired from, that other system, and has not previously exercised an
8 irrevocable election to remain a member of the Louisiana State Employees'
9 Retirement System pursuant to R.S. 11:160 through 417 for the same
10 employment. The system shall produce all necessary forms for this purpose.
11 (2) Any employee who makes a timely election to join this system
12 pursuant to this Subsection has the same rights as any other system member to
13 enter into a reciprocal recognition agreement pursuant to R.S. 11:142 or
14 transfer service credit pursuant to R.S. 11:143, provided however, that no
15 person who transfers service credit to this system shall have the right to execute
16 a reverse transfer pursuant to the provisions of R.S. 11:143(F)(1).
17 Section 2. The provisions of R.S. 11:1903 shall authorize approval of any district or
18 parish court covering designated classes of employees even if other positions paid with funds
19 of the court are required by law to be members of other public retirement systems. Any
20 member currently enrolled in another public retirement system shall be given until January
21 1, 2027, to make an irrevocable election to become a member of the Parochial Employees'
22 Retirement System of Louisiana or remain a member of their prior system.
